  <description type="morphology">Plants (7–)13–41(–61) cm. Leaves: basal spatulate, acute to obtuse, margins entire-crenate to crenate; cauline (2–)4–13(–24), proximal lanceolate to narrowly spatulate, (26–)44–102(–185) × (4–)5.7–12(–21.5) mm, margins serrate; mid to distal (7.8–)10.1–60(–132) × 1–8(–15.5) mm, margins entire or finely serrate distally. Heads in open wandlike to congested paniculiform arrays. Peduncles: bracteoles 1–3(–4). Phyllaries: shortest (1.4–)1.8–2.7(–3.4) mm. Cypselae sparsely strigose. 2n = 36.</description>
